    <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to my trail running site!</h1>
    <p>Trail running is an incredible way to stay active while immersing yourself in nature, offering both physical and mental benefits that go beyond a typical workout. The soft, uneven terrain reduces the impact on your joints compared to pounding pavement, helping to prevent common road-running injuries. As you weave through trees, climb hills, and navigate winding paths, you engage a variety of muscles, improving strength, balance, and endurance. Beyond the physical perks, trail running is a powerful way to clear your mind—free from traffic, noise, and daily stressors, you can focus on the rhythm of your breath and the beauty of the outdoors. Whether it's the fresh air, the peaceful solitude, or the sense of adventure, hitting the trails leaves you feeling refreshed, recharged, and ready for whatever comes next.</p>


